sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / CI
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Webhook as Webhook Server<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Controller as Controller Manager<br/>controller-runtime
    participant Driver as Spark Driver Pod
    participant Executor as Spark Executor Pods<br/>7078, 7079/TCP

    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
        Note over User,Executor: Flow 1: SparkApplication Submission
        User->>K8sAPI: 1. kubectl apply SparkApplication<br/>HTTPS/443 | Bearer token
        K8sAPI->>Webhook: 2. Admission review (mutate + validate)<br/>HTTPS/9443 | TLS | API server mTLS
        Webhook->>K8sAPI: 3. Set defaults, validate spec<br/>HTTPS/443 | TLS | ServiceAccount token
        K8sAPI-->>Controller: 4. Watch event: SparkApplication created
        Controller->>K8sAPI: 4. Reconcile: create driver pod<br/>HTTPS/443 | TLS | ServiceAccount token
        Controller->>Driver: 5. spark-submit execution<br/>Process exec
        Note over Driver: Driver starts running
        Driver->>K8sAPI: 6. Request executor pods<br/>HTTPS/443 | TLS | SA: spark-operator-spark
        K8sAPI->>Webhook: 7. Admission review (mutate pods)<br/>HTTPS/9443 | TLS | API server mTLS
        Note over Webhook: Inject volumes, env vars,<br/>sidecars, monitoring config,<br/>security contexts
        Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Pod mutated
        K8sAPI-->>Driver: Executors created
        Driver->>Executor: 8. Task distribution<br/>TCP/7078, 7079 | No encryption
        Executor-->>Driver: Task results
        Driver-->>Controller: Application completed
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Update status, cleanup (TTL)
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
        Note over User,Executor: Flow 2: ScheduledSparkApplication Cron Execution
        Note over Controller: Cron timer fires
        Controller->>K8sAPI: 1. Check concurrency policy<br/>HTTPS/443 | TLS | ServiceAccount token
        Controller->>K8sAPI: 2. Create child SparkApplication CR<br/>HTTPS/443 | TLS | ServiceAccount token
        Note over Controller: 3. SparkApplication reconcile loop<br/>(follows Flow 1 steps 4-8)
    end

    rect rgb(230, 255, 230)
        Note over User,Executor: Flow 3: SparkConnect Server Lifecycle
        User->>K8sAPI: 1. Create SparkConnect CR<br/>HTTPS/443 | TLS | Bearer token
        K8sAPI-->>Controller: Watch event: SparkConnect created
        Controller->>K8sAPI: 2. Create ConfigMap (executor pod template)<br/>HTTPS/443 | TLS | ServiceAccount token
        Controller->>K8sAPI: 3. Create server Pod<br/>HTTPS/443 | TLS | ServiceAccount token
        Controller->>K8sAPI: 4. Create Service (4 ports)<br/>7078, 7079, 4040, 15002/TCP
        participant Client as Spark Connect Client
        Client->>Driver: 5. Connect to Spark Connect server<br/>TCP/15002 | Spark Connect protocol | No encryption
    end
